International Brief -- Finmeccanica S.p.A.:
   Italian Firm to Go Public
   After Merging With Unit
Finmeccanica is wholly owned by the state holding company
Istituto per la Ricostruzione Industriale.
   Finmeccanica also said it will pay IRI 719 billion lira in
compensation for the subsidies it received in the mid-1980s
for car maker Alfa Romeo S.p.A. The subsidies were declared
illegal by the European Court of Justice last year. The
company sold Alfa Romeo to Fiat S.p.A. in 1987.
   As a result of the payment, Finmeccanica said it posted a
consolidated loss of 525 billion lira for 1991, compared with
a profit of 120 billion lira in 1990.